  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment: 12 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 1 factor carried as not-assessed on the grounds that it is argued to be inapplicable to a purely computational sensitivity study — however, the encoding correctly reflects the absence of assessment rather than a formal scoping decision.",
